WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:01.384
Alright!

00:00:01.384 --> 00:00:04.068
Let's set up SSH keys so you

00:00:04.068 --> 00:00:06.369
can reach your servers without passwords.

00:00:06.369 --> 00:00:07.903
This is pure SSH;

00:00:07.903 --> 00:00:09.438
rdc isn't involved yet.

00:00:10.205 --> 00:00:11.200
Two ideas.

00:00:11.200 --> 00:00:14.186
Generate one key on your laptop,

00:00:14.186 --> 00:00:17.171
then authorize it on each server

00:00:17.171 --> 00:00:18.166
with ssh-copy-id.

00:00:18.166 --> 00:00:19.161
Generate once,

00:00:19.161 --> 00:00:20.654
copy per server.

00:00:23.907 --> 00:00:24.363
First,

00:00:24.363 --> 00:00:27.100
generate a new SSH key on

00:00:27.100 --> 00:00:28.012
your laptop.

00:00:28.012 --> 00:00:29.381
Ed25519 is secure,

00:00:29.381 --> 00:00:29.837
small,

00:00:29.837 --> 00:00:31.205
and well supported.

00:00:31.205 --> 00:00:33.030
You do this once;

00:00:33.030 --> 00:00:35.767
the same key works for every

00:00:35.767 --> 00:00:37.135
server you add.

00:00:37.135 --> 00:00:38.960
This is plain SSH,

00:00:38.960 --> 00:00:41.696
nothing to do with rdc yet.

00:00:42.496 --> 00:00:43.115
Key generated.

00:00:43.115 --> 00:00:45.897
The public half is what we copy to each

00:00:45.897 --> 00:00:46.206
server.

00:00:49.555 --> 00:00:52.453
Now authorize the key on your first

00:00:52.453 --> 00:00:53.694
server with ssh-copy-id.

00:00:53.694 --> 00:00:56.592
It appends your public key to the

00:00:56.592 --> 00:00:57.834
server's authorized list,

00:00:57.834 --> 00:01:00.317
so future logins skip the password.

00:01:02.317 --> 00:01:04.094
Authorized on the first server.

00:01:04.094 --> 00:01:05.870
No more password prompts there.

00:01:09.207 --> 00:01:12.098
Do the same for every other server

00:01:12.098 --> 00:01:12.924
you manage.

00:01:12.924 --> 00:01:15.402
Here we authorize the second one.

00:01:15.402 --> 00:01:17.880
Just repeat ssh-copy-id for each machine.

00:01:19.880 --> 00:01:21.988
Both servers now trust this key.

00:01:21.988 --> 00:01:23.746
SSH is fully set up.

00:01:24.584 --> 00:01:27.215
Your key is set and your servers

00:01:27.215 --> 00:01:27.967
trust it.

00:01:27.967 --> 00:01:28.719
Next up,

00:01:28.719 --> 00:01:31.350
we add your first server to rdc.
